Response to
Episode 3 - "When Knowledge Conquered Fear"
@-------------------------------------------------
I wonder if humanity will still exist on Earth to see the Milky Way-Andromeda
Collision, and if so, how much we would have changed. Who knows what will
happen in those billion years? If something cause humans to go extinct as the
dinosaurs did, or how evolution would run its course? There is some comfort in
knowing that none of us will be alive to see that future, supposing that it
is far away.

This video first exposed me to the conflict between Robert Hooke and Isaac
Newton. History makes big names out of them, listing out their spectacular
accomplishments, but these petty rivalries and blatant lies are what bring
them back to earth (no pun intended) and show that they are flawed, just
like any other human.

I wonder what it's like to invent calculus.
